  <section id="bio">
    <h2>About Me</h2>
    <p>Born and raised in Shamshernagar, Sylhet, Bangladesh, I began my graduate journey in 2018 at Khulna University of Engineering and Technology (KUET), specializing in Industrial Engineering. Over four & half years, I gained hands-on expertise in supply chain optimization, digital tools, operations management through research and real-world projects.</p>
    <p>My academic contributions include four published research articles on sustainable & resilient supply chains, and emerging technologies.</p>
    <p>Professionally, I worked as a Supply Chain Production Planning Engineer at Akij Plastics Ltd. Now, as a <strong>PhD student</strong> in Hydrogen Supply Chain at Warwick University (WMG), I am committed to advancing sustainability research while expanding my professional network and expertise.</p>
